cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for horizon/skyline detection, which is a common problem in robotics and autonomous navigation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves transfer learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in robotics and autonomous systems, hence cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves geographical and environmental challenges, which can be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
